-- Brazilian Stock Movers: Amil Participacoes, Cetip Were Active
-- B y   Z a c h a r y   T r a c e r
-- 2012-03-12T20:43:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-12/brazilian-stock-movers-amil-cetip-hypermarcas-are-active.html
The following companies had  unusual 
price changes in Sao Paulo trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close of trading. Preferred
shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The  Bovespa (IBOV)  Index fell 0.5 percent to 66,384.76.  Amil Participacoes SA (AMIL3)  (AMIL3 BS) dropped 1.6 percent to
18.70 reais. The health insurer was cut to neutral from buy by
analysts including Joao Carlos dos Santos at Banco BTG Pactual
SA, according to a research note today. The analysts cited
“gloomier operating prospects” and the company’s valuation.  Cetip SA - Mercados Organizados (CTIP3)  (CTIP3 BS) fell 3.9 percent
to 32 reais.  Brazil ’s biggest securities clearing house was cut
to equal weight from overweight by analysts including Henrique Caldeira at  Barclays Capital , according to a research note
today. The rating indicates that Barclays expects the stock to
perform in line with its sector, according to the note.  To contact the reporter on this story:
